    "description": "Join the HomeLane family as a SEO Specialist in Bengaluru. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout HomeLane:\nHomeLane is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor and improve Net Promoter Score (NPS) and customer satisfaction\n• Manage email marketing campaigns and push notifications\n• Analyze sales data and customer behavior to drive revenue growth\n• Execute digital marketing campaigns across Google, Meta, and other channels\n• Coordinate with vendors and suppliers for inventory management\n• Develop and implement category growth strategies\n• Create engaging content for product pages and social media\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• BPharm / MPharm / PharmD\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Email Marketing\n• Proficiency in Google Analytics\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in Influencer Marketing\n• Proficiency in Affiliate Marketing\n• Proficiency in WooCommerce\n• Proficiency in Performance Marketing\n• Proficiency in A/B Testing\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Flexible working hours\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with HomeLane!",
